President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama extend their best wishes to Muslims in the United States and around the world for a joyful Eid al-Adha. They also congratulate the millions of peaceful pilgrims performing the Hajj, including thousands of American Muslims. The President acknowledges that throughout the year, Muslims, alongside members of many faiths, serve those suffering from hunger, disease, and conflict. He emphasizes that Muslim communities will continue this practice during Eid by distributing food and charity to those in need. The President believes that these acts of compassion highlight the shared values of the Abrahamic religions and people of all faiths. On behalf of the American people, he extends warm greetings for the holiday, saying, "Eid Mubarak."